<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="394" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,433,748]" pageId="13" pageNumber="394">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,577,603]" pageId="13" pageNumber="394">Distribution.</emphasis>
The whole territory of 
<collectingCountry box="[621,755,577,603]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="13" pageNumber="394">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
, mountains of Central Asia; in the extreme northwest of the range reaches Southern Urals and Lower Volga Region, 
<collectingCountry box="[809,887,613,639]" name="Russia" pageId="13" pageNumber="394">Russia</collectingCountry>
. In Southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[1091,1222,613,639]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="13" pageNumber="394">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
was found in low mountains and in river valleys in the plains.
</paragraph>
